Hi Endi,

Sorry for the late reply.
This is not a real error, just a warning. If you use the program as
is, some of the features on your monitor will not be available through
gddccontrol.
But the basic things like brightness, contrast and color are pretty
much always available.

The thing is, there are no active maintainers for the project, me
included, and adding monitors to the database is quite a long process.
Plus we do not have a debian/ubuntu packager, so there is pretty much
no hope of having the new database installed in the distributions
through repos.

Cheers,

Will

